cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about jointly learning semantic parsing and natural language generation, which are both sub-tasks of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel method of dual information maximization, which involves regularization and optimization techniques, suggesting that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of variational lower bounds, which is a common technique in neural networks and deep learning, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper experiments with dialogue management and code generation, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
